title: Over and Out
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Restless little one
Comfortable and warm
Let me fall apart
Crippled in your arms
[Pre-Chorus 1]
Chase me through the dark
Ready on your mark
First to reach the stars
Wins a broken heart, one that broke apart
Shattered from the start
[Chorus]
Are you there?
Do you read me?
Are you there?
I don't feel you anymore
[Verse 2]
Cages and alarms
Keepin' us from harm
I will be the guard
Hope to rest upon
[Pre-Chorus 2]
Could I be the one
To break a will so strong?
Pray it won't be long
'Til your will is gone,
 everythin' is done
Nothin' left at all

[Chorus]
Are you there?
Do you read me?
Are you there?
I don't feel you anymore
Are you there?
Will you give in
Are you there?
If I give out?
[Post-Chorus]
(Ooh-ooh-ooh)
Over and out
(Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh)
[Bridge]
Cages and alarms
Keepin' us from harm
I will be the guard
Hope to rest upon, everythin' is done
Nothin' left at all
[Chorus]
Are you there?
Do you read me?
Are you there?
I don't feel you anymore
Are you there?
Will you give in
Are you there?
If I give out?
